1. Objective\par
Develop a backend API for a Library Management System that can add, view, update, delete, and search book records.\par
\par
2. Technology Stack\par
- Node.js and Express.js\par
- MongoDB and Mongoose\par
- dotenv\par
- Postman\par
- GitHub and Render\par
\par
3. REST API Endpoints\par
- POST /books : Add a new book\par
- GET /books : View all books\par
- GET /books/:id : Get one book by ID\par
- PUT /books/:id : Update book details\par
- DELETE /books/:id : Delete a book\par
- GET /books/search?title=xyz : Search by title\par
- GET /books/search?author=xyz : Search by author\par
\par
4. Features Implemented\par
- Book schema validations\par
- Unique ISBN\par
- Proper HTTP status codes\par
- Error handling middleware\par
- Async/await and try/catch in controllers\par
- Render deployment blueprint\par
